<blockquote>Molycorp is a Delaware limited liability company with headquarters in Greenwood Village, Colorado, and is a private, US mining and technology company that produces and markets rare earth products. Molycorp is primarily owned by Resource Capital Fund IV L.P., Pegasus Partners IV, LP, The Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. and Traxys North America LLC. As the owner of one of the world's richest rare earth deposit outside of China and a leader in rare earth technology development, Molycorp's expertise has provided breakthroughs in industries as varied as military, computing and automotive. As the leading western supplier, Molycorp markets rare earth materials from its world class rare earth deposit and mining operation in Mountain Pass, California. In addition, Molycorp maintains a joint venture with Sumitomo Metals, called Sumikin Molycorp, which markets rare earth products in Asia and produces permanent magnet materials in Japan.</blockquote>

