<p>Secrecyâ€”and alleged secrecyâ€”is as much an issue in the trial as partisanship. â€œYou used the statement several times that they have a secret, concealed relationship with CapAd,â€ the judge, Thomas Hogan, asked Bredhoff. â€œYou get that from where?â€</p>
<p>â€œThis is not known to the general public,â€ argued Bredhoff. â€œThe reason they donâ€™t want it out there is because it completely contradicts their message, which they promulgate constantly. It was not known to anybody until this litigation began, and itâ€™s been agreed by the parties in the course of this litigation that that fact remain secret.â€</p>
