At the behest of  his governmentâ€™s lobbyist, Premier Ewart Brown of Bermuda met in June with key congressmen, among them the powerful House Ways and Means chairman, Charles Rangel, D-N.Y., and two Democrats from states in <a href=""http://www.hurricanealley.net/HAnaclimo.htm"">hurricane alley</a>, G.K. Butterfield of North Carolina and Bennie Thompson of Mississippi.

The sessions, Brown boasted later in Bermudaâ€™s Royal Gazette, were part of a â€œvery successful tripâ€ that included â€œmeetings with people who were not even on the schedule.â€

