 pretty much the same handful of lawmakers going back to 1993. It appears that Rep. John Murtha (<a href=""http://www.opensecrets.org/indivs/search.asp?key=ffqw4&amp;txtState=(all%20states)&amp;txtCand=murtha&amp;txtEmploy=dsd%20lab&amp;txtAll=Y&amp;Order=N"">$22,000</a>) and Rep. Alan Mollohan (</a><a href=""http://www.opensecrets.org/indivs/search.asp?key=xpu6a&amp;txtState=(all%20states)&amp;txtCand=mollohan&amp;txtEmploy=dsd%20lab&amp;txtAll=Y&amp;Order=N"">$16,150</a>)have gotten the bulk of the contributions, with Rep. Marty Meehan (<a href=""http://www.opensecrets.org/indivs/search.asp?key=39pgb&amp;txtState=(all%20states)&amp;txtCand=meehan&amp;txtEmploy=dsd%20lab&amp;txtAll=Y&amp;Order=N"">$14,000</a>) coming in third. If I were curious about who inserted each earmark for DSD Laboratories, I might begin by asking those three members.

